@jitinl: In Beancount, prices aren't kept around after the transaction - so to keep track of the cost basis, you'll need to use the cost syntax (see the [Beancount language syntax documentation](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1wAMVrKIA2qtRGmoVDSUBJGmYZSygUaR0uOMW1GV3YE0/edit#heading=h.mtqrwt24wnzs))

> maybe for "market value" and "currency" conversions, an option to say when the conversion happens should be given, and a user can select "at posting time", "at aggreation end" (for bar charts), "at the end of the reporting period (not know if this is useful?)

Allowing a date to be specified to be used for the conversions is tracked in #1048 (the examples you give are basically the default right now, when a date can be inferred, we use that).
